subject: p16662264
History: Hypoxia, tachypnea and reported infiltrate on outside film though not available for comparison. Assess for infectious process or other etiology of hypoxia.
Findings: Lungs are low in volume. Congestion of the pulmonary vasculature, small bilateral pleural effusions and presence of septal lines reflects mild pulmonary edema. Consolidations in the right mid lung and retrocardiac location could reflect a concurrent pneumonia. Cardiac size is top normal with a normal cardiomediastinal silhouette.
Impression: Bilateral consolidations could reflect a multifocal infectious process. Bilateral small pleural effusions with mild pulmonary edema.
